# Q-MIND — Deep-Tech Startup Plan

## One-Liner

**Q-MIND is the verification layer for artificial intelligence: a symbolic engine that computes, proves, and explains — with zero hallucination.**

---

## The Problem — in one sentence

> LLMs hallucinate math. CAS tools are inaccessible. Nobody verifies AI output.

| Pain Point | Who Feels It | What They Do Today |
|------------|-------------|-------------------|
| ChatGPT/Claude can't guarantee 2+2=4 | Students, engineers, researchers | Double-check manually or pray |
| CAS tools require `Integrate[f[x],{x,0,1}]` syntax | Everyone outside academia | Give up, trust the LLM |
| No way to verify AI-generated math claims | Regulated industries (finance, engineering) | Hire human auditors at $200/hr |
| Math tools don't speak Portuguese | 260M+ lusophone speakers | Use English or nothing |

**Core insight:** In a world of probabilistic AI, deterministic symbolic reasoning becomes a premium layer — not a competitor to LLMs, but a **complement**.

